dc:subject: Cranium
Female
Thin Bone
Asymmetrical Vault
dc:description: Cranium has a highly worn RP4 and LM1, and there is resorption of molar and premolar alveoli. Overall the cranium is very light-weight due to bone loss: the superior bony vault is visibly smoothed ("eroded"), and the right temporal squama, palatines, and orbital plates are paper-thin. The pterygoid plates may have contacted the posterior sphenoid or petrosals. Palatine foramina are expanded, and the vault is grossly asymmetrical.

dc:memberOf.title: Ford Collection, UM Museum of Anthropological Archaeology
